                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The reason people are in favor of keeping the variables as tight as possible (in this case using the same mob for all testing, the only variable being charisma) is due to the fact that it is the ONLY way to get a definitive result on how charisma and only charisma can effect charm.  That means we want to keep the mob's level/MR and caster level the same (even the charm spell) changing -only- the charisma statistic.<br /><br />If you run off and do another test on a different mob in Veksar or anywhere else, then you run into the possibility of a different level, different magic resist, etc..  You can certaintly do this, but it is not necessary to reach a conclusive decision on how charisma affects charm at all.<br /><br />Remember we're looking -only- at how charisma effects charm.  Not how does it effect charm on 5 different mobs all with different MR and levels.<br /><br />With that said,  my opinion is that charisma is worthless for a necro and only mildly useful for lull spells.  Mine is high enough to get max price from a merchant and only because I'm too lazy to swap in mugs and it just kinda worked out that way with my gear setup.<br /><br />The fact that WoT sucked in that test at lower charisma is due to the nerf on the spell and the inherent randomness of charm.  Do another 10 tests and you're just as likely to find that higher charisma makes the spell seem less effective.<br /><br />Lich Nakht Takharu - Arch Lich - 7th Hammer</span id="msg"></font></td>
